text:
Battery Park: A northeastward view towards State Street from the Sea Wall. Buildings shown lining this confine of the Park are: the United States Custom House, the Battery Park Building (No. 21-24 State Street) and the Chesebrough Building (No. 15-19 State Street). This set consists of 2 views.

October 7, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Manhattan: Battery Park - State Street (Northeast).
